Reasoning: The paper discusses the edge sign prediction problem in social networks and proposes an algorithm to recover the clustering with high probability in the presence of noise. This problem falls under the scope of social network analysis and machine learning, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) are the most likely categories as they directly relate to social network analysis. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also relevant as the paper proposes an algorithmic solution to the problem. Finally, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but it could be relevant if the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed algorithm in a system or control setting.
